Product description

Color:Gray  |  Style:Flip Advanced 4-in-1 Carrier

Product Description

Infantino Flip Advanced 4-in-1 Convertible Carrier Product Description Adjustable: Yes Color: Grey Weight Limit: 8-32 lbs Closure type: Full-buckle closure Materials: Polyester and cotton Dimensions: (HxWxD) 15 x 10.0 x 2.0 Inches Weight: 1 lbs Care and Cleaning: Machine Wash Warning: Failure to follow the manufacturer’s instructions can result in death or serious injury. Read all instructions before assembling and using your carrier. Keep instructions and review them before attempt- ing new carrying positions. Always keep one hand on baby while adjusting carrier. Never use when bal- ance or mobility is impaired. Fall and Suffocation Hazard Fall Hazard: Infants can fall through wide leg opening or out of carrier. Adjust leg openings to fit babies legs snugly Before each use, make sure all knots and fasteners are secure Never bend at waist, bend at knees Only use carrier for babies between 8 lbs and 32 lbs Suffocation Hazard: Infants under 4 months can suffocate in this product if face is pressed tight against your body. Do not strap infant too tight against your body Allow room for head movement Keep infant’s face free from obstructions at all times Care Instructions: Machine wash cold, separately, on gentle cycle with mild detergent. Do not bleach. Wipe clean with cloth or sponge between machine washings. Drip dry only. Do not iron.

      How are ratings calculated?
      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Jessica
      5.0 out of 5 stars Works well for newborn, with a small hack
      Reviewed in the United States on September 12, 2017
      Color: GrayStyle: Flip Advanced 4-in-1 CarrierVerified Purchase
      I'm taking my 2 week old around the neighborhood in this carrier and she fits well into it, with a small hack. Unlike some other carriers, you do not need an infant insert with this infatino. The straps tighten enough to offer good support for a newborn at the back and neck. One problem is that it kind of cuts out my baby's blood circulation in the legs. You can watch the little feet turn purple in a few minutes... BUT, we found a hack - roll up a towel or small blanket and put it at the bottom of the carrier as a booster seat. That way the legs can bend down naturally instead of forced into a split. As the baby get bigger and her blood circulation improves, you can remove the booster. Overall great carrier at great price, easy to put on and my baby always falls asleep in it. By the time she’s 5 months and weighs about 15lbs, we switched to ergo as she can fit in it without an insert and it’s more comfortable for the adult.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Happy baby
      Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2018
      Color: GrayStyle: Flip Advanced 4-in-1 CarrierVerified Purchase
      We’ve tried 4 baby carriers.

      Lillebaby all seasons 6 position carrier: seat too wide for baby to sit comfortably (practically doing the splits) and it was very expensive ($140)

      Baby K’tan: worked okay when our baby was a newborn but there’s zero adjustability so my husband couldn’t use it at all, it was outgrown too quickly ($50)

      Infantino sash wrap and tie: by far the easiest for both parents to put on, inexpensive, easily adjustable, but can’t carry baby facing out on the front, and most of the weight is placed on lower back. I never wore this for longer than 30min but definitely a winner for babies who aren’t ready to face out. ($35)

      Infantino Flip 4-in-1 Convertible Carrier: Now that our baby is 9 months old, this is our go to carrier. She loves looking at the world as we go for long walks. Carries the weight evenly on shoulders and back, easy to adjust, but be careful of the extra space you take up, I did bonk her head going sideways through a door. ($30)

      3.0 out of 5 stars Lightweight and easy to use but has its drawbacks.
      Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2018
      Color: GrayStyle: Flip Advanced 4-in-1 CarrierVerified Purchase
      We also have an Ergo 360 and how our son fits in them is a bit different but mainly the Ergo has much more padding in the hip and shoulders and keeps him more snug against my body. The main positive for the Infantino is that its lightweight and you don't get nearly as hot as you do in the Ergo. At 5 months old the kid has more room to move his head around and I don't sweat as much as I do with the Ergo, but I don't think I could wear this for 2 hours without back pain but I could in the Ergo.

      All in all I'm glad I got it and I'd buy it again. The Ergo is more comfortable but its also $120 more.

      A bigger and more supple pad on the waist band would go a long way. Maybe DIY it?

      Ambrosia
      4.0 out of 5 stars Great Price, Comfortable, and Functional
      Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2015
      Color: GrayStyle: Flip Advanced 4-in-1 CarrierVerified Purchase
      For the price, you really can't go wrong. I bought this for a vacation to Florida where it would have been way to hot to use a wrap that we had been using.

      PROS:

      Price- If you want to make sure that your baby will like a soft structured carrier and aren't ready to invest in a nicer expensive one, this is the carrier for you. Or if you never want to spend a lot of money on a carrier, you will still get decent quality with this.

      Lightweight- the material is breathable and the carrier itself does not weigh much. I was able to wear for long periods of time in the hot Florida summer heat without overheating myself and baby.

      Versatile- The leg openings are adjustable for small babies and larger babies. All four straps that secure arms and legs are adjustable. Both straps that clip around parent are adjustable. I'm 5'5" and my husband is 6'4" and we are both able to easily adjust this to fit comfortably.

      4 ways to wear- easy instructions and videos to help you wear baby safely. There is head support that folds down and snaps for when facing baby out. Both front positions and hip carry are easy to do by yourself, back carry needs assistance. ***We have not personally tried back carry yet as she is you small still. ***

      Washable- Very easy to machine wash without ruining.

      CONS

      Drool cover- Basically worthless. It's supposed to be able to attach both forward and inward facing, but the Velcro is only on one side of the cloth so it doesn't really work facing in. Plus it falls off easily anyways either way is attached. Not the biggest deal in the world, but it definitely is a useless feature.

      Shoulder straps- They are padded, which is nice, but it's not terribly thick or overly soft padding. It worked fine for our little baby, but I can't imagine using this for long periods of time once she hits 17-20#. The style of the strap is not the most ideal either. It's basically like backpack straps with a thin strap that buckles across your upper back. More expensive carriers will have x shaped straps or straps that actually cross over to help disperse weight better. But again, for the price it's nice to try out or use sparingly once the baby is heavier.

      Overall it was a good buy and I would recommend to anybody not wanting to spend a lot of money or trying out a soft structure carrier to test. We have since invested in a Beco Gemini, which is a very similar style, and also use a ring sling and Solly wrap for wearing at home, but we still use this carrier.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Game changer
      Reviewed in Canada on August 11, 2017
      Color: GrayStyle: Flip Advanced 4-in-1 CarrierVerified Purchase
      This is my 4th baby carrier (moby, ring sling, ergo original). I've only had it for a short while, but it is already worth the money. The other carriers were either too big to fit my newborn (ergo without insert) or too hot (all of them) in the summer heat. This carrier definitely has more airflow and I am able to take my 2 big dogs on a walk in the summer heat without worrying about my baby overheating. There are a lot of clips involved, but there are lots of videos on how to put it on by yourself. Once you get the hang of it, it's so easy and fast. I think if you are new to baby carrying, and you don't want to spend a tonne of money, this is a great place to start.
